VAIFORM — STORYBOARD / PREVIEW / RENDER UI RULES

Applies to:
- web/public/creative.html
- web/public/creative.css
- web/public/js/pages/creative/creative.article.mjs
- related storyboard/preview UI files

Rules:
- playbackTimelineV1 remains backend-owned timing truth.
- previewReadinessV1 remains backend-owned readiness truth.
- Frontend must consume these truths, not recreate them.
- UI/layout changes must not weaken preview parity or render gating.
- Duration-based visual widths may be transitional, but must derive from backend-owned timing data only.
- Keep selected-clip actions scoped to selection, not duplicated everywhere.
- Do not change backend render/finalize semantics in a UI pass.
